<paragraph id="4E7036DFFFF6153403B6FB19DB3F0258" blockId="13.[151,1437,1182,1929]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">
<bibRefCitation id="2A5E4B2EFFF6153403B6FB19DE53038C" author="Distant, W. L." box="[151,314,1182,1208]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" pagination="360 - 376" refId="ref19630" refString="Distant, W. L. (1909) Rhynchota (Heteroptera) from British India. Annales de la Societe entomologie de Belgique, 53, 360 - 376. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 21876" type="journal article" year="1909">Distant (1909)</bibRefCitation>
described the new genus 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF61534017FFB19DC1E038C" authority="Distant, 1909" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1909" box="[606,887,1182,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Isdegardes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF61534017FFB19DDB1038C" box="[606,728,1182,1208]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Isdegardes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2A5E4B2EFFF6153401FEFB19DC1E038C" author="Distant, W. L." box="[735,887,1182,1208]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" pagination="360 - 376" refId="ref19630" refString="Distant, W. L. (1909) Rhynchota (Heteroptera) from British India. Annales de la Societe entomologie de Belgique, 53, 360 - 376. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 21876" type="journal article" year="1909">
Distant, 
<quantity id="89379B3AFFF61534001EFB19DC1E038C" box="[831,887,1182,1208]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.84886" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" unit="in" value="1909.0">1909</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in an unspecified subfamily for a single species, 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF6153403B6FB45DD1903E8" authority="Distant, 1909" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1909" box="[151,624,1218,1244]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Isdegardes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanocephalus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF6153403B6FB45DEA603E8" box="[151,463,1218,1244]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Isdegardes melanocephalus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2A5E4B2EFFF6153402F7FB45DD1903E8" author="Distant, W. L." box="[470,624,1218,1244]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" pagination="360 - 376" refId="ref19630" refString="Distant, W. L. (1909) Rhynchota (Heteroptera) from British India. Annales de la Societe entomologie de Belgique, 53, 360 - 376. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 21876" type="journal article" year="1909">Distant, 1909</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from Calcutta. Regarding, generic affinities, he noted only “This genus is somewhat allied to 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF6153402ADFB61DE9A0234" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[396,499,1254,1280]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Reduvius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF6153402ADFB61DE9A0234" box="[396,499,1254,1280]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Reduvius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.” A conspicuous feature of this new taxon was “anterior tibiae…somewhat broadly compressed and curved”. In the appendix to 
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF6153401A8FA8DDCDC0210" box="[649,949,1290,1316]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">
The Fauna of 
<collectingCountry id="36D8764FFFF615340006FA8DDCDC0210" box="[807,949,1290,1316]" name="India" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">British India</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="2A5E4B2EFFF6153400E2FA8DDB0C0210" author="Distant, W. L." box="[963,1125,1290,1316]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" refId="ref19675" refString="Distant, W. L. (1910) The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Rhynchota. - Vol. V. Heteroptera: Appendix. Taylor &amp; Francis, London, 362 pp." type="book" year="1910">Distant (1910)</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF61534079DFA8DDE7E027C" authority="in Acanthaspidinae" authorityName="in Acanthaspidinae" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Isdegardes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF61534079DFA8DDA5F0210" box="[1212,1334,1290,1316]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Isdegardes</emphasis>
in Acanthaspidinae
</taxonomicName>
“to follow 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF6153402B2FAA9DE93027C" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[403,506,1326,1352]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Reduvius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF6153402B2FAA9DE93027C" box="[403,506,1326,1352]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Reduvius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” in the key from his previous treatment (i.e., 
<bibRefCitation id="2A5E4B2EFFF6153400CEFAA9DBEB027C" author="Distant, W. L." box="[1007,1154,1326,1352]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" refId="ref19591" refString="Distant, W. L. (1904) The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Rhynchota. - Vol. II (Heteroptera). Taylor &amp; Francis, London, 503 pp." type="book" year="1904">Distant 1904</bibRefCitation>
), at the same time including a figure of the dorsal habitus and lateral view of the head (
<bibRefCitation id="2A5E4B2EFFF61534006EFAD5DC8D0258" author="Distant, W. L." box="[847,996,1362,1388]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" refId="ref19675" refString="Distant, W. L. (1910) The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Rhynchota. - Vol. V. Heteroptera: Appendix. Taylor &amp; Francis, London, 362 pp." type="book" year="1910">Distant 1910</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 109).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="06D56554FFF6153403E6FAF0DE6A00BD" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" type="description">
<paragraph id="4E7036DFFFF6153403E6FAF0DC6701B8" blockId="13.[151,1437,1182,1929]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">
It is clear from this habitus figure that Distant had placed his new genus in the wrong subfamily, as 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF615340603FAF1DAF502A4" box="[1314,1436,1398,1424]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Isdegardes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF615340603FAF1DAF502A4" box="[1314,1436,1398,1424]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Isdegardes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is congeneric with the peiratine genus 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF615340164FA1DDC5B0280" authority="Stal, 1863" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[581,818,1433,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Phalantus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF615340164FA1DDDDE0280" box="[581,695,1434,1460]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Phalantus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2A5E4B2EFFF61534019FFA1EDC5B0280" author="Stal, C." box="[702,818,1433,1460]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" pagination="25 - 58" refId="ref22036" refString="Stal, C. (1863) Formae speciesque novae reduviidum. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, Quatrieme Series, 3, 25 - 58." type="journal article" year="1863">Stål, 1863</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The curved and compressed protibia are a distinct feature of 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF6153403CBFA39DE3502EC" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[234,348,1470,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Phalantus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF6153403CBFA39DE3502EC" box="[234,348,1470,1496]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Phalantus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF6153402FBFA39DD2302EC" authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[474,586,1470,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Peiratinae">Peiratinae</taxonomicName>
are most often diagnosed by the transverse pronotal suture being distinctly behind the middle (versus at or before middle in 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF615340196FA65DC5202C9" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1807" box="[695,827,1506,1533]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Reduviinae">Reduviinae</taxonomicName>
), this suture is situated very nearly at the middle of the pronotum in species of 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF615340280F981DD7A0114" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[417,531,1542,1568]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Phalantus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF615340280F981DD7A0114" box="[417,531,1542,1568]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Phalantus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(compare 
<figureCitation id="D6F42A5AFFF6153401ADF981DD890114" box="[652,736,1542,1568]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1175,1200]" captionTargetBox="[195,1437,191,1154]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1437,191,1155]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Comparison between Isdegardes (Reduviinae) and Phalantus (Peiratinae): (A) Isdegardes melanocephalus, line drawing of habitus after Distant (1910); (B) Phalantus africanus, adult male. Scale bar =2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3548408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3548408/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Two other species of 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF6153400C6F981DB300114" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[999,1113,1542,1568]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Phalantus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF6153400C6F981DB300114" box="[999,1113,1542,1568]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Phalantus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known from 
<collectingCountry id="36D8764FFFF61534063CF981DA320114" box="[1309,1371,1542,1568]" name="India" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">India</collectingCountry>
: 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF615340647F981DEA70170" authority="Distant, 1903" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Phalantus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="feanus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF615340647F981DE440170" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Phalantus feanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2A5E4B2EFFF615340217F9ADDEA70170" author="Distant, W. L." box="[310,462,1578,1604]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" pagination="43 - 65" refId="ref19557" refString="Distant, W. L. (1903) Contributions to a knowledge of the Rhynchota. Annales de la Societe entomologie de Belgique, 47 (4), 43 - 65." type="journal article" year="1903">Distant, 1903</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF615340126F9ADDCE80170" authority="Stal, 1863" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[519,897,1577,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Phalantus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geniculatus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF615340126F9ADDC6B0170" box="[519,770,1578,1604]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Phalantus geniculatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2A5E4B2EFFF61534002AF9AEDCE80170" author="Stal, C." box="[779,897,1577,1604]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" pagination="25 - 58" refId="ref22036" refString="Stal, C. (1863) Formae speciesque novae reduviidum. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, Quatrieme Series, 3, 25 - 58." type="journal article" year="1863">Stål, 1863</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus id="9174887DFFF6153400E0F9ACDC980171" box="[961,1009,1579,1605]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF615340753F9ADDB850170" box="[1138,1260,1578,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Isdegardes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF615340753F9ADDB850170" box="[1138,1260,1578,1604]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Isdegardes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is, for the time being, considered distinct from these based on having the legs wholly ochraceous; in 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF61534077AF9C8DBA9015C" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1903" box="[1115,1216,1614,1640]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Phalantus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="feanus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF61534077AF9C8DBA9015C" box="[1115,1216,1614,1640]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">P. feanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF6153407D9F9C8DAFC015C" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[1272,1429,1614,1640]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Phalantus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geniculatus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF6153407D9F9C8DAFC015C" box="[1272,1429,1614,1640]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">P. geniculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the apices of the femora and base of the tibiae are black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4E7036DFFFF6153403E6F911DE6A00BD" blockId="13.[151,1437,1182,1929]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">
Given the evidence outlined above, 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF61534017CF911DB5A0184" authority="Distant, 1909" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1909" box="[605,1075,1686,1712]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Isdegardes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanocephalus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF61534017CF911DCFD0184" box="[605,916,1686,1712]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Isdegardes melanocephalus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2A5E4B2EFFF6153400BDF911DB5A0184" author="Distant, W. L." box="[924,1075,1686,1712]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" pagination="360 - 376" refId="ref19630" refString="Distant, W. L. (1909) Rhynchota (Heteroptera) from British India. Annales de la Societe entomologie de Belgique, 53, 360 - 376. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 21876" type="journal article" year="1909">Distant, 1909</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF615340647F911DE3301E0" authority="Stal, 1863" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Phalantus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF615340647F911DFB201E0" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Phalantus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2A5E4B2EFFF6153403C5F93EDE3301E0" author="Stal, C." box="[228,346,1721,1748]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" pagination="25 - 58" refId="ref22036" refString="Stal, C. (1863) Formae speciesque novae reduviidum. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, Quatrieme Series, 3, 25 - 58." type="journal article" year="1863">Stål, 1863</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, resulting in 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF6153402CEF93DDC7601E0" authorityName="Swanson" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[495,799,1722,1748]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Phalantus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanocephalus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF6153402CEF93DDC7601E0" box="[495,799,1722,1748]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Phalantus melanocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF615340009F93DDCC301E0" bold="true" box="[808,938,1722,1748]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="678857B6FFF615340009F93DDCC301E0" box="[808,938,1722,1748]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
This act relegates 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF6153407A3F93DDAF501E0" authority="Distant, 1909" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1909" box="[1154,1436,1722,1748]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Isdegardes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF6153407A3F93DDB9501E0" box="[1154,1276,1722,1748]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Isdegardes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2A5E4B2EFFF615340625F93DDAF501E0" author="Distant, W. L." box="[1284,1436,1722,1748]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" pagination="360 - 376" refId="ref19630" refString="Distant, W. L. (1909) Rhynchota (Heteroptera) from British India. Annales de la Societe entomologie de Belgique, 53, 360 - 376. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 21876" type="journal article" year="1909">Distant, 1909</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
to a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF6153402BFF959DDE101CC" authority="Stal, 1863" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[414,648,1757,1784]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Phalantus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF6153402BFF959DD7901CC" box="[414,528,1758,1784]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Phalantus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2A5E4B2EFFF615340137F95ADDE101CC" author="Stal, C." box="[534,648,1757,1784]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" pagination="25 - 58" refId="ref22036" refString="Stal, C. (1863) Formae speciesque novae reduviidum. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, Quatrieme Series, 3, 25 - 58." type="journal article" year="1863">Stål, 1863</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF6153401AEF959DD9F01CC" bold="true" box="[655,758,1758,1784]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">syn. nov.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2A5E4B2EFFF6153401DCF959DCF301CC" author="Distant, W. L." box="[765,922,1758,1784]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" pagination="360 - 376" refId="ref19630" refString="Distant, W. L. (1909) Rhynchota (Heteroptera) from British India. Annales de la Societe entomologie de Belgique, 53, 360 - 376. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 21876" type="journal article" year="1909">Distant (1909</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="2A5E4B2EFFF615340084F959DCB701CC" author="Distant, W. L." box="[933,990,1758,1784]" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" refId="ref19675" refString="Distant, W. L. (1910) The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Rhynchota. - Vol. V. Heteroptera: Appendix. Taylor &amp; Francis, London, 362 pp." type="book" year="1910">1910</bibRefCitation>
) generally mentioned similarities to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF6153403C0F885DE210028" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[225,328,1794,1820]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Reduvius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF6153403C0F885DE210028" box="[225,328,1794,1820]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Reduvius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but drew no other generic comparisons. However, the obvious similarities with 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF6153407FDF885DA270028" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[1244,1358,1794,1820]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Phalantus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF6153407FDF885DA270028" box="[1244,1358,1794,1820]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Phalantus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would have necessitated comparison with 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF615340109F8A1DDCB0074" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1909" box="[552,674,1830,1856]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Isdegardes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF615340109F8A1DDCB0074" box="[552,674,1830,1856]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Isdegardes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. I have speculated that Distant considered only reduviines after assessing the transverse pronotal suture, despite clearly having been aware of 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF6153400C8F8CDDB320050" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[1001,1115,1866,1892]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Phalantus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF6153400C8F8CDDB320050" box="[1001,1115,1866,1892]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">Phalantus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as he had already described 
<taxonomicName id="89CF4D5CFFF6153403B6F8E8DF9500BC" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1903" box="[151,252,1902,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Phalantus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="feanus">
<emphasis id="7CBBEACDFFF6153403B6F8E8DF9500BC" box="[151,252,1902,1928]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="209">P. feanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
